runs = api.runs(
    "qcp-assenagon/qcp-assenagon-project",
    filters={
        "summary.std_objective": {"$exists": True},
        "config.solver.type": {"$exists": True}
    }
)
```

The `$exists` operator checks if a field exists, which is what you want when filtering for runs with those values set. According to the API documentation, `$exists` is a supported MongoDB query operator.

