In TypeScript, use `weave.op` to wrap both functions and class methods. For class methods, wrap them in the constructor:

```typescript
import * as weave from 'weave'

class MyClass {
    constructor() {
        this.myMethod = weave.op(this.myMethod)
    }

    myMethod(name: string) {
        return `Hello, ${name}!`
    }
}
```

This works for any method on a class, automatically tracking all calls whether they're functions or methods.

